subSubSection.paragraph:
In Oakland, California, the beetles were found in a backyard in an urban environment with non-native grasses and a mixture of native and non-native shrubs. Collections were made during the day, and the specimens were found in leaf litter around a small coffeeberry (
Frangula californica
), under a birdbath on moist soil, and at the base of dandelions (
Taraxacum officinale
).
